name: 遺跡の戦士, 遺跡の戦士

parameters: \N<Irime>...hah.

For a moment, it seemed like Irime's footing faltered.
Probably the result of the Ryuda soldiers at the barracks,
who must have drugged her just enough to go unnoticed as
promised.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Irime>You understand, don't you, Segi? There's no need to go easy
on me. This is that kind of battle.
\N<Segi>Yes... I understand, Miss Irime.
\N<Irime>Haah... haah...
\N<Segi>Irime-san... are you okay?

\N<Irime>Fu, fufu... It's nothing. It's quite something to worry
about your opponent in the middle of a battle.

\N<Segi>It's not "your opponent" I'm worried about. I'm concerned
about you, Irime-san.
\N<Irime>Segi...

\N<Segi>(That's right... I must not hurt Irime-san more than
necessary. I need to find a way to safely subdue her by
depleting her stamina...)

\N<Irime>Haah... haah...! My body won't listen to me...!? Segi...
could it be you...!?

\N<Segi>...As you've guessed. I've taken the liberty of making a
slight adjustment to your body, Miss Irime.

\N<Segi>But please don't worry. It's just a small amount of poison
that will naturally be expelled from your body after a
little time. However... right now, even standing should be
quite difficult for you.

\N<Segi>Miss Irime... shall we call an end to this battle here?
Would you be willing to lay down your weapon...?

\N<Irime>I see... so you did this to avoid injuring me more than
necessary...

\N<Irime>Fu, fufu... I see. When our battle was decided... and when I
stood before you on this stage...

\N<Irime>I didn't have the luxury to be considerate of my opponent...
and I thought there was no need for it. Yet you...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Irime>I see... this battle was lost by me from the very beginning,
wasn't it...
\N<Zozoie>...Ah...?

For a moment, it seemed like Zozoie's footing faltered. It
was likely the result of the Ludan soldiers at the outpost
drugging him just enough to go unnoticed, as promised.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zozoie>Heh heh... Now then, shall I show you some affection? If you
admit defeat now, I might let you off with just a beating.
But in the end, you'll still become my female slave, heh
heh.

\N<Segi>...We'll see about that. I'll teach you that not everything
in this world goes your way.
\N<Zozoie>Ah!!??
\N<Zozoie>Guh...ugh? What's...happening to my body...?
\N<Segi>Haa...haa...It seems to have finally taken effect.
\N<Zozoie>Is this your doing...what the hell did you do...?

\N<Segi>I didn't do anything special. Perhaps it's the grudge of the
many people you've hurt that's affecting you now?
\N<Zozoie>Tch...so it's you, the woman from that time...!?

\N<Zozoie>You slipped something in during the confusion, didn't you?
No wonder things felt off...

\N<Segi>If that's the case, you should have been more cautious. Did
you let your guard down because I'm a woman? How foolish.

\N<Zozoie>You...I won't let this slide, getting cocky just because
you're a woman...!

\N<Segi>That's exactly what I mean...acting all high and mighty just
because you're a man!
\N<Segi>Zuuteruka...!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... What's with that fighting spirit, Segi? You're not
seriously thinking you can beat me, are you?

\N<Segi>I wouldn't be standing here if I thought I'd lose! And I
certainly don't intend to show any disgrace in front of Lord
Yuia!

\N<Zuuteruka>I see... You're still misunderstanding something, aren't
you?
\N<Segi>What do you mean...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>You don't actually believe that if you beat me, everything
that's happened to you up until now will just disappear, do
you?

\N<Zuuteruka>To get to this place, you were violated by men whose names
you don't even know. To fight me in this place, you spread
your legs for a man you call your sworn enemy. How many men
have violated you, defiled you, toyed with you?

\N<Zuuteruka>Do you think that if you beat me, all of that will be wiped
clean and you'll return to a life filled with smiles with
your husband and son?
\N<Segi>Haa... Haa!!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... It's useless, you know? No matter how much spirit
you show, it all ends in vain.

\N<Zuuteruka>Didn't I tell you? Even if you defeat me, what has happened
to your body won't just disappear.

\N<Zuuteruka>The Mind Luda infesting your body erodes it day by day...
The Luda's lewd decorations etched into you will always
confront you with the reality that you were a courtesan, no
matter how much you try to forget.

\N<Zuuteruka>With your body defiled by men... do you seriously think you
can now share true love with Yuia...?

\N<Segi>Haa... Haa!! Even if everything can't go back to the way it
was...!
\N<Segi>You, who are responsible for this... I will defeat you...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... That's a fairy tale! Do you seriously think you
can beat me?!

\N<Segi>I do think so...! And now I have the possibility to do so!
No, now is the only time I have that possibility...!

\N<Segi>You yourself have taught me that! The effects of Mind Luda
are at their peak right now...!

\N<Segi>This spiritual medicine induces arousal and at the same time
enhances physical strength! That means... along with the
erosion of arousal, my own power is at its peak right now,
isn't it?!
\N<Zuuteruka>...I see.

\N<Zuuteruka>...Indeed, that's correct. You've been thinking about
various things too, huh... Hehehe.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Feels empty, doesn't it? Even if you defeat me,
you can't erase the past of being my mistress.

\N<Zuuteruka>I took your virginity... and even after you became a mother,
I continued to dote on you as my mistress.

\N<Zuuteruka>I've explored every inch of your body, there's not a single
place that hasn't been touched by my tongue or fingers.
That's how much you exist because of me.
\N<Segi>Even if... that's true...
\N<Zuuteruka>Oh...?

\N<Segi>The past where you defiled me...! The reality of being toyed
with by you that can never be erased, even if it's a fact!

\N<Segi>For my father and mother... for Lord Yuia and the many
others you've brought misfortune to...!

\N<Segi>For their sake, I cannot break! Even if I'm violated or
defiled, I can't bow down to someone like you and face
them!!

\N<Segi>No matter what misfortunes there are, I must keep my head
up...! No matter what past there is, I must move forward...!
Otherwise, I can't go on living!!

\N<Segi>As myself...!! I can't live if I despair in unhappiness and
turn away from what's important!!!
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... So you're going to live as yourself, huh?

\N<Zuuteruka>Interesting... Then show me! Show me how far you can embody
those noble ideals after being played with by me and other
men!
\N<Segi>I will...!!
\N<Segi>Why...!? Why did you tell Riia about this battle...!?

\N<Rozaro>Isn't it obvious that he needs to be mentally prepared? To
face the reality that his mother has been sacrificing
herself for him, and that right now, she's about to become
another man's property.

\N<Segi>How selfish... That won't help him prepare at all! It will
only hurt his heart and tear apart his tender chest!

\N<Rozaro>And what if it does? The more wounded a person is, the
easier it is to ensnare them. What if that was my aim?
\N<Segi>I won't forgive you... I will never forgive you!

\N<Rozaro>Haha, don't make grandiose statements. Those are words meant
for those who have the power to surpass their opponents.
\N<Segi>Haah... Haah...

\N<Rozaro>What's wrong, Segi-san? Your movements are getting sluggish
from fatigue, aren't they?

\N<Segi>So strong... They're incomparable to anyone I've faced
before...

\N<Segi>But... I can't afford to be downhearted. It's precisely in
times like these that I must have confidence. Even I have
been able to strike back against such a formidable
opponent...

\N<Segi>That said... We'll get nowhere like this. If it turns into a
war of attrition, Rozaro-san, with his superior stamina,
will have an absolute advantage.
\N<Segi>There must be something... some way to break through...

\N<Segi>Remember... Remember, Segi. Even if I have to dredge up
those sunken memories by force... I must remember.
\N<Segi>Haa... haa...

\N<Segi>Remember... remember, Segi. There must be... there must be a
breakthrough somewhere...
\N<Rozaro>...

\N<Segi>That's right... that night... the night I first met Mr.
Rozaro...

\N<Segi>He was being chased by Zeda and his gang, and he came to the
clinic... and then... that's when I protected him...

\N<Segi>At that time... he had suffered a terrible injury to his
eye...
\N<Segi>Which was it... which one...
Right eye
Left eye
右眼
\N<Segi>That's right... I remember now...

\N<Segi>...Mr. Rozaro's facial scar was from that time. And he said
his right eye's vision hadn't fully recovered...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Segi>But still... it's too dangerous. But there's no other
choice... that's right, I never thought it would be safe to
win from the start...
左眼

\N<Segi>The left eye... or the right eye...? No good... I can't
remember...
\N<Rozaro>Ugh...!?
\N<Segi>Haah...! Haaah!

\N<Rozaro>I see... You exploited the narrow field of vision from the
old wound in my right eye.

\N<Segi>You wouldn't call it cowardly, would you...? Targeting an
opponent's weakness is a basic tactic in battle.

\N<Rozaro>Heh... It seems I underestimated you. And I also misjudged
the passion you have for this fight.

\N<Rozaro>From here on out... I'll be getting a bit more serious,
alright? Prepare yourself to be humiliated in front of my
son!

\N<Irime>Segi, you understand, right? There's no need to go easy on
me. This is that kind of battle.
\N<Segi>Yes... I understand, Irime-san.
\N<Irime>Haa... haa...
\N<Segi>Are you okay, Irime-san?

\N<Irime>Fu, fufu... It's nothing. It's quite something to worry
about your opponent in the middle of a battle.

\N<Segi>I'm not worried about 'my opponent'. I'm worried about you,
Irime-san.
\N<Irime>Segi...

\N<Segi>(That's right... I must not hurt Irime-san more than
necessary. I need to find a way to deplete her stamina and
somehow subdue her safely...)

\N<Irime>Haah... haah...! My body won't listen to me...!? Segi...
could it be you...!?

\N<Segi>...As you've guessed. I've taken the liberty of making a
slight adjustment to your body, Miss Irime.

\N<Segi>But please don't worry. It's just a small amount of poison
that will naturally be expelled after some time. However...
right now, even standing should be quite difficult for you.

\N<Segi>Miss Irime... shall we call an end to this battle here?
Would you be willing to lay down your weapon...?

\N<Irime>I see... so you did this to avoid injuring me more than
necessary...

\N<Irime>Fu, fufu... I see. When the fight with you was decided...
and when I stood on this stage facing you...

\N<Irime>I didn't have the luxury to be considerate of my opponent...
and I thought there was no need for it. Yet you...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Irime>I see... this battle was lost by me from the very beginning,
wasn't it...
\N<Segi>Huh!?

\N<Zozoie>Heh heh... Well then, shall I show you some love? If you
admit defeat now, I might let you off with just a half-
killing. But in the end, you'll still become my female
slave, heh heh.

\N<Segi>...I wonder about that. I'll teach you that not everything
in this world goes your way.
\N<Zozoie>Ahh!!??
\N<Zozoie>Guh...ugh? What's... happening to my body...?
\N<Segi>Haah...haah...It's finally taking effect, it seems.
\N<Zozoie>Is this your doing... What the hell did you do...?

\N<Segi>I didn't do anything special. Perhaps it's the grudge of the
many people you've hurt until now that's affecting you?
\N<Zozoie>Tch... I see, you're that woman from back then...!?

\N<Zozoie>You slipped something in during the confusion, didn't you?
No wonder I felt something was off...

\N<Segi>If that's the case, you should have been more cautious. You
let your guard down because I'm a woman, didn't you? Truly
foolish.

\N<Zozoie>You... I won't let this slide, getting cocky just because
you're a woman...!

\N<Segi>That's exactly what I'm talking about... acting all high and
mighty just because you're a man!
\N<Segi>Huh?!

\N<Segi>My body is slimy and dullly shining... Is that... like an
oily substance covering my body...?

\N<Segi>If that's the case... it might be weak to something that
could ignite...
\N<Segi>Haa... haa...
\N<Fubii>Not bad, auntie. Better than I imagined.
\N<Segi>...Didn't I tell you not to underestimate adults?

\N<Fubii>Yeah, it seems so. It looks like I was the one being licked
after all.

\N<Fubii>Those eyes... they're just like hers. Eyes that don't doubt
what they believe in.
\N<Fubii>What is it... it's really getting on my nerves.
\N<Segi>That woman...? Who on earth are you talking about...?
\N<Fubii>Does it matter? It's none of your business, ma'am.

\N<Segi>...You're talking about the woman from the orphanage where
you spent time, aren't you?
\N<Fubii>...And what if I am?

\N<Segi>Let me ask you something... You loved that woman, didn't
you?
\N<Fubii>Loved her? Me? That woman?

\N<Fubii>Ahaha, don't be ridiculous. I was just trying to see through
her true nature.

\N<Fubii>She was kind to everyone, but in return, she'd easily sway
to anyone. Such a shallow nature of a woman.

\N<Segi>Don't make me laugh, that's not the nature of women. That's
just... strictly her own way of living.
\N<Segi>After all... I'm different. I'm not like that woman.

\N<Segi>I might not be able to be kind to everyone, but at least I
don't just sway with anyone.
\N<Fubii>...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Segi>Why don't you be a little more honest with yourself? What
you really wanted wasn't to discern someone's true nature,
nothing so grandiose.

\N<Segi>It's just a tantrum because the person you loved wasn't the
ideal you had in mind.

\N<Segi>Understand? It's all because of your immaturity, lumping
everything you see and hear into one.
\N<Fubii>...That's not it.

\N<Segi>No, it's not different. After all, you're running away from
the woman at the heart of the problem and your mother who
abandoned you. You're lashing out at people who have nothing
to do with it.

\N<Segi>You're averting your eyes from those you should be
confronting... What else would you call that if not
immaturity?

\N<Fubii>What would I call it...? Don't spout nonsense when you don't
understand anything...?
\N<Segi>...
\N<Fubii>I... I...!!
Fubii's expression is showing signs of agitation...!
\N<Fubii>I went... to save that woman!
\N<Segi>...

\N<Fubii>Because I thought she was suffering! Because I thought she
was being oppressed by those bandits!

\N<Fubii>And yet... when I went to save that woman! She was
frightened... frightened of me who had killed the bandits!

\N<Fubii>That woman, completely trained by the bandits...! She denied
me who had come to rescue her!
\N<Segi>...

\N<Fubii>That's when I realized! That's the nature of women! My
mother who abandoned me... and that woman who pretended to
care! Both are despicable, tainted beings!

\N<Fubii>And you, auntie, are the same! Even now, acting all
innocent, eventually you'll spread your legs just as easily
for me or for the Ryuda, won't you!

\N<Fubii>Forgetting about your husband and son, choosing pleasure
instead! That's the irresistible nature of you women!!
\N<Segi>...
\N<Segi>Haa... Haa...

\N<Hojiko>...You're quite persistent, aren't you, Segi-san. It seems I
underestimated you, thinking you were a powerless woman.

\N<Hojiko>By the way, I heard you spoke with my wife the other day.
What exactly did you talk about?
\N<Segi>That is...
I said I love you.
I was told to lose for your sake.
貴方を愛していると言っていた
\N<Segi>Your wife... she said she loves you.

\N<Segi>She cares deeply for you... and she was praying for your
safety.
\N<Hojiko>She loves me? She's praying for my safety?
\N<Segi>...Yes.
\N<Hojiko>Fu... Fufu, hahaha!

\N<Hojiko>What are you talking about! That can't be true! She loves
me, you say!? Don't spout such blatant lies!
\N<Segi>I merely... spoke the truth.
\N<Hojiko>...
You can see a look of disturbance on Hojiko...!
貴方の為に負けて欲しいと言われた

\N<Segi>Your wife... seemed surprised that her opponent was me. And
at the same time, she also seemed relieved...
\N<Hojiko>Relieved? What do you mean by that?

\N<Segi>Your wife asked me to lose to her. She said that if it were
me, I would surely grant her wish.

\N<Hojiko>Oh...? I see, considering your kindness, of course, you
would do that for her, right? You would grant my wife's
wish?
\N<Segi>I cannot... I simply cannot do that, just that one thing...

\N<Hojiko>...I see. Then it seems we must fight and settle this once
and for all.
\N<Segi>...Hojiko-san. Could you spare a moment to listen to me?

\N<Hojiko>What is it, Segi-san? You're not begging for your life at
this point, are you?
\N<Segi>That's not it... but you may take it that way if you wish.
\N<Hojiko>What do you mean...?
\N<Segi>...Please take a look at this.

Segi took out a glowing scale she had harvested from a
monster in the ruins and held it out to Hojiko as she
continued.

\N<Hojiko>What's this...? What are you trying to do by showing me
something like this now?

\N<Segi>This is something I found by chance in the ruins. I don't
understand its value, but perhaps you do?
\N<Hojiko>That is... a part of an extremely rare mineral.

\N<Segi>I thought so. It's something I took from a monster inside
the ruins, and I thought it might be valuable.
\N<Hojiko>So what... what are you getting at?

\N<Segi>I do not wish to continue fighting any longer. If you agree
with me, then this battle could be rendered pointless.

\N<Segi>Of course, I'm not suggesting this for free. If you withdraw
here... I will give this to you.
\N<Hojiko>What did you say...?

\N<Segi>This is valuable, isn't it? Wouldn't it be beneficial for
you to keep it?
\N<Hojiko>...
\N<Segi>...
\N<Hojiko>I see... so this is your way of making a deal.

\N<Hojiko>Understood... You might be right. If more people abandon the
fight, those from Ryuda might reconsider the very purpose of
the training assembly.
\N<Segi>...Then.

\N<Hojiko>Alright... I'll accept it as the promised item of our
agreement.
\N<Segi>Eh...!?
\N<Hojiko>Wha...!?

The dull glowing scale melted away in Hojiko's palm in no
time, and both of them were astonished by the sight.

\N<Hojiko>You... you tricked me! How dare you, a woman! Trying to
curry favor with me with such a fake! You vixen!
\N<Segi>No, that's not it... I...
\N<Hojiko>Shut up! Who would listen to any more of this?!
\N<Segi>(Hojiko-san's eyes are burning with anger towards me...)
\N<Segi>(But... stay calm. Calm down, Segi.)
\N<Segi>(Yes... perhaps this could actually be an opportunity...)

Hojiko is furious, his hand holding his weapon is
trembling...!

\N<Segi>Haa... haa... It's okay... I should be able to do it if I
calm down.

\N<Segi>Besides... if I stumble here, I won't be able to protect
what's important later on.

\N<Segi>Th-that's right... The thing I received from Mr. Rozaro...
it might come in handy at a time like this...!
